Brainfuck interpreter for linux kernel


1. Compilation

   $ make

2. Loading module

   # make load

3. Usage examples

   $ echo ">++++++[<++++++++>-]>++[<+++++>-]<[<.+>-]" > /proc/brainfuck/code
   $ cat /proc/brainfuck/output 
   0123456789

   $ echo ",[>,]<[.<]" > /proc/brainfuck/code
   $ echo -n "abcdef" > /proc/brainfuck/input
   $ cat /proc/brainfuck/output 
   fedcba

4. unloading module

   # make unload
